e": "A-diagnostics", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: Messages for errors, warnings, and lints"}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 7, "created_at": "2018-03-10T13:28:25Z", "updated_at": "2019-01-26T01:02:00Z", "closed_at": "2019-01-26T01:02:00Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Just an idea: \r\n\r\nLet's say our code looks like this:\r\n````rust\r\nfn main() {\r\n\t{\r\n\t\t{\r\n\t\t\t{\r\n\t\t\t\tprintln!(\"Hello, world!\");\r\n\t\t}\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n````\r\nThe error message is not very helpful here, pointing to lines 1 and 8:\r\n````\r\nerror: this file contains an un-closed delimiter\r\n --> src/main.rs:8:3\r\n  |\r\n8 | }\r\n  |   ^\r\n  |\r\nhelp: did you mean to close this delimiter?\r\n --> src/main.rs:1:11\r\n  |\r\n1 | fn main() {\r\n  |           ^\r\n\r\n````\r\n\r\nHowever, since cargo inits new repos as git repo, *maybe* we can utilize the repo diff and see which brace was added the last:\r\n```` diff\r\n fn main() {\r\n        {\r\n                {\r\n-                       println!(\"Hello, world!\");\r\n+                       {\r\n+                               println!(\"Hello, world!\");\r\n                }\r\n        }\r\n }\r\n````\r\nand give a better diagnostic:\r\n\r\n````\r\nerror: this file contains an un-closed delimiter\r\n --> src/main.rs:8:3\r\n  |\r\n8 | }\r\n  |   ^\r\n  |\r\nhelp: did you mean to close this delimiter?\r\n --> src/main.rs:4:12\r\n  |\r\n4 |                 {\r\n  |                 ^\r\n```\r\n", "closed_by": {"login": "estebank", "id": 1606434, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE2MDY0MzQ=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1606434?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/estebank", "html_url": "https://github.com/estebank", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/estebank/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/estebank/followi